HB 649 Engrossed 2026 Regular Session Brass
Abstract: Requires the Bd. of Regents to establish a statewide application process for dual
enrollment programs.
Present law requires the Bd. of Regents, in consultation with the State Bd. of Elementary and
Secondary Education, to promulgate rules for and administer a dual enrollment grant
program.
Present law specifies that it does not prohibit a local public school board from entering an
interinstitutional articulation and transfer agreement with a public postsecondary education
institution relative to dual enrollment.
Proposed law retains present law.
Proposed law requires the Bd. of Regents, in coordination with La. public postsecondary
education institutions, to establish a statewide application process for students to apply to
participate in dual enrollment programs.
Proposed law requires every public postsecondary education institution to participate.
Provides exception if written notice is provided to an institution's management board.
(Amends R.S. 17:2943)
